        "authorId" : "085a9c6b-569e-49bd-9434-7f128372cf0c",
        "body" : "I'm not sure what `cb3` is, but very recently I built a package `noarch: python` that was py3 only and found that I could install it on py2. This prompted a change in the docs:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/conda-forge/conda-forge.github.io/pull/483\r\n\r\nstating that `skip` selectors were not allowed with `noarch`. ",
        "createdAt" : "2017-11-11T13:08:56Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2017-11-11T13:08:56Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "085a9c6b-569e-49bd-9434-7f128372cf0c",
